The article provides excerpts from the opening statement of Mike Pompeo, the Director of the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA), during his testimony before the U.S. Senate Committee on Foreign Relations. Pompeo discusses various topics, including his commitment to working closely with the committee, his gratitude for serving as the leader of the CIA, his plans to empower the diplomatic corps at the State Department, his focus on strengthening the workforce culture and communication, and his belief in America's duty to lead in democracy, prosperity, and human rights. He also addresses being labeled a "hawk," the diplomatic efforts to resolve the North Korean nuclear threat, countering Iran's dangerous behavior and fixing flaws in the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA), Russia's aggressive actions and future diplomatic efforts, and working diplomatically with China for a more productive bilateral partnership.